BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260411T084200
DTEND:20260411T181800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.991ft at 08:42\n-2.965ft at 18:18\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Size holds as primary SSW swell and secondary WNW swell continues and some
  new windswell joins in. Widespread waist to shoulder high+ waves\, as sta
 ndouts hit 1-2' overhead. Dawn patrol high tide slows tide sensitive break
 s\, getting better as the morning tide ebbs. \n\nUnfortunately\, there wil
 l also be SW-SSW winds through the day\, light+ for the dawn patrol\, mode
 rate by mid morning\, then getting breezy in the afternoon for sloppy cond
 itions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260412T094200
DTEND:20260412T183000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.935ft at 09:42\n-2.992ft at 18:30\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 A storm moving into the coast kicks up a peaking W windswell\, as SSW Sout
 hern Hemi lingers and WNW swell fades. That mix looks good for jumbled sur
 f running head high+ at average spots\, while better exposures are consist
 ently overhead in the morning. Slow fading but still punchy waves over the
  afternoon. \n\nRight now the call is for moderate+ SW winds for a bumpy m
 orning\, then some improvement during the day as the onshores back off a b
 it. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260413T103000
DTEND:20260413T183600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.988ft at 10:30\n-2.964ft at 18:36\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Easing combo of SSW swell and shorter-period WNW swell is still good for w
 idespread chest to shoulder high waves in the morning\, as top breaks are 
 head high. Surf will taper off over the afternoon along with the fading sw
 ell. Early morning will be slowed by high tide. Ebbing tide helps through 
 mid day. \n\nLight offshores due much of the morning\, followed by a light
 + WSW afternoon sea breeze. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260414T112400
DTEND:20260414T184200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.918ft at 11:24\n-2.922ft at 18:42\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Old blend of SSW swell and shorter-period WNW swell is down to leftovers\,
  mainly running thigh to waist high. Mid morning high tide bogs down the s
 maller surf\, then ebbing tide helps some through mid day.\n\nLight/variab
 le winds early morning\, shifting side shore westerly mid-day\, then offsh
 ore NW over the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
